assistant > To solve the expression \((1\$8)\$10\), we need to follow the defined operation \(a\$b = 1 \times a + 1 \times b\).

First, calculate \(1\$8\):
\[ 1\$8 = 1 \times 1 + 1 \times 8 = 1 + 8 = 9 \]

Next, use the result to calculate \(9\$10\):
\[ 9\$10 = 1 \times 9 + 1 \times 10 = 9 + 10 = 19 \]

So, the result of \((1\$8)\$10\) is 19.

\[ \text{<<<1, \$, 8, \$, 10, =, 19>>>} \]
